---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Newsletter from '../components/Newsletter.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Money — Financial Sovereignty"
  description="The Money pillar at AfterChildren. Retirement math, Medicare, Social Security, long-term care, estate planning, housing decisions — the financial structure that has to outlast you, because nobody else is going to build it for you."
>
  <!-- PILLAR HERO -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="pillar-hero">
      <p class="pillar-hero__eyebrow">Sovereignty 02</p>
      <h1 class="pillar-hero__title">
        Money.<br />
        <em>The fuel that has to outlast you.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="pillar-hero__lede">
        Your money has to last 30 years, possibly without working income, possibly through one major care event, possibly through two. The retirement math you were taught in the 1990s is no longer adequate. The Medicare you assume will cover you does not cover what most people think it covers. The estate plan you wrote in 2009 probably does not do what you believe it does. This is the section of the site where we tell you what actually works, in numbers, with no advertiser pressure.
      </p>
      <div class="pillar-hero__meta">
        <span><span class="pillar-hero__count">20</span> planned articles in this pillar</span>
        <span class="pillar-hero__sep">·</span>
        <span><span class="pillar-hero__count">2</span> live now</span>
        <span class="pillar-hero__sep">·</span>
        <span>Updated weekly</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHERE TO START -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="start-panel">
      <p class="start-panel__eyebrow">Where to start</p>
      <h2 class="start-panel__title">Three steps. This quarter. Not next year.</h2>
      <ol class="start-panel__list">
        <li class="start-panel__item">
          <span class="start-panel__num">01</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="start-panel__step">Run your numbers</h3>
            <p class="start-panel__desc">Total retirement assets, expected Social Security, planned working years left, projected ordinary spending, projected long-term care exposure. Most people have never done this with real precision. Most plans fail because of that gap.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="start-panel__item">
          <span class="start-panel__num">02</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="start-panel__step">Hire a fiduciary, once</h3>
            <p class="start-panel__desc">Fee-only, no commissions, no product sales. Pay $2,500 to $5,000 for a one-time comprehensive plan. The single highest-ROI financial expense available to anyone over 55 who has not done this. Avoid anyone whose income depends on selling you an annuity.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="start-panel__item">
          <span class="start-panel__num">03</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="start-panel__step">Plan long-term care while you are healthy</h3>
            <p class="start-panel__desc">The Medicaid five-year lookback rule means asset planning has to happen by your early 60s. The LTC insurance application gets harder every year you wait. The CCRC entry decision is best made in your late 60s. None of this can wait until you need it.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FEATURED ARTICLE -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="featured">
      <p class="featured__eyebrow">Start here</p>
      <a href="/money/medicare-advantage-vs-medigap-2026" class="featured__card">
        <div class="featured__meta">
          <span class="featured__tag">Tier 1 · Live</span>
          <span class="featured__time">16 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="featured__title">Medicare Advantage vs Medigap: The Honest Comparison for 2026</h2>
        <p class="featured__excerpt">The decision that locks in for life — and the marketing that obscures it. The five dimensions that actually matter, the case for each, the 2026 rule changes, and the honest answer for most healthy 65-year-olds. Without the broker-commission distortion.</p>
        <span class="featured__cta">Read the article <span class="featured__arrow">→</span></span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE SIX MONEY SUB-PILLARS -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="subpillars">
      <p class="subpillars__eyebrow">The six money domains</p>
      <h2 class="subpillars__title">The financial sovereignty work, broken down.</h2>

      <div class="subpillar">
        <div class="subpillar__head">
          <span class="subpillar__num">01</span>
          <h3 class="subpillar__title">Retirement math</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subpillar__intro">The 4% rule is dead for anyone retiring after 2025. The real safe withdrawal rate is closer to 3.3%. That $7,000 gap, year after year, is what catches people 12 years into retirement, with no time left to recover. The math has to be rerun with current assumptions, not 2014 ones.</p>
        <ul class="subpillar__list">
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> The 4% Rule Is Outdated — Here's What Replaces It</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> The Retirement Math Most Parents Get Catastrophically Wrong</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Should You Pay Off the Mortgage Before Retirement?</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Roth Conversions in Your 60s: When It Makes Sense</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Required Minimum Distributions: The Tax Bomb at 73</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="subpillar">
        <div class="subpillar__head">
          <span class="subpillar__num">02</span>
          <h3 class="subpillar__title">Medicare &amp; health insurance</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subpillar__intro">Most people get the Medicare decision wrong on first enrollment and never undo it. Medicare Advantage looks cheaper and locks you in. Medigap is more expensive on paper and protects you on the back end. The decision depends on health, geography, and risk tolerance — not on the TV commercials.</p>
        <ul class="subpillar__list">
          <li class="subpillar__item--live"><a href="/money/medicare-advantage-vs-medigap-2026">Medicare Advantage vs Medigap: The Honest Comparison for 2026</a></li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Medicare Enrollment Deadlines: The Penalties Nobody Warns You About</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Medicare Timing When One Spouse Still Works</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Health Savings Accounts for Pre-Retirees: The Underused Lever</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="subpillar">
        <div class="subpillar__head">
          <span class="subpillar__num">03</span>
          <h3 class="subpillar__title">Social Security</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subpillar__intro">The claiming decision is worth, on average, $100,000 to $200,000 over a 30-year retirement. Most people claim at 62 because they can. Most should not. The right age depends on your health, your spouse's health, your other income, and your longevity expectation — and almost never on what the local advisor recommends, because the local advisor is not the one who will live with the consequences.</p>
        <ul class="subpillar__list">
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Social Security Claiming Strategy: When to Take It</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Spousal and Survivor Benefits Most People Miss</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Working While Drawing Social Security: The Rules</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="subpillar">
        <div class="subpillar__head">
          <span class="subpillar__num">04</span>
          <h3 class="subpillar__title">Long-term care</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subpillar__intro">70% of people 65+ will need some form of long-term care. Average duration: 3 years for men, 3.7 for women. Average annual cost in 2026: $75,000 to $124,000 depending on setting. Medicare does not cover this beyond 100 days. The middle class falls into a planning gap that has only four real solutions, and three of them require action by age 65.</p>
        <ul class="subpillar__list">
          <li class="subpillar__item--live"><a href="/manifestos/adult-children-not-retirement-plan">The Hardest Truth: Your Adult Children Are Not Your Retirement Plan</a></li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Long-Term Care Insurance: Is It Worth It? (The Real Math)</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Medicaid Planning: The Five-Year Lookback Rule Explained</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Hybrid Life/LTC Insurance: When It Makes Sense</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> The Real Cost of Aging in Place vs. Assisted Living</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="subpillar">
        <div class="subpillar__head">
          <span class="subpillar__num">05</span>
          <h3 class="subpillar__title">Estate &amp; inheritance</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subpillar__intro">Most wills do not do what their authors think they do. About 60% of American adults have no will at all. Of those who do, half wrote it more than 10 years ago. The Power of Attorney, Healthcare Directive, HIPAA authorization, and digital estate documentation that you do not have are the documents your family will desperately need at the worst possible moment. None of this is optional. Most of it can be done for under $400 online.</p>
        <ul class="subpillar__list">
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Estate Planning Without a Lawyer: What You Can DIY (And What You Can't)</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Why Your Will Alone Isn't Enough: The Documents You're Missing</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> The Inheritance Conversation Nobody Wants to Have</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> How to Protect Your Money From an Adult Child's Bad Marriage</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> The Estate Tax Threshold: What It Means for You</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="subpillar">
        <div class="subpillar__head">
          <span class="subpillar__num">06</span>
          <h3 class="subpillar__title">Housing finance</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="subpillar__intro">The house is the largest asset most parents own and the most emotionally loaded financial decision of the second half. Downsize too early, lose the place that anchors your community. Downsize too late, leave value on the table and face a forced move from weakness. Reverse mortgages can be a lifeline or a trap depending on the structure. The math has to be done with a clear head, while there is still time to do it.</p>
        <ul class="subpillar__list">
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Reverse Mortgage: The Pros, Cons, and Who It Actually Helps</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> Downsizing the Family Home: The Financial Truth</li>
          <li><span class="subpillar__soon">Coming</span> The Sandwich Generation Trap: Funding Both Sides</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE TRUTH WE COMMIT TO -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="commitments">
      <p class="commitments__eyebrow">Our money-content rules</p>
      <h2 class="commitments__title">What we promise on every financial page.</h2>
      <div class="commitments__grid">
        <div class="commitment">
          <h3 class="commitment__title">No commissioned recommendations</h3>
          <p class="commitment__desc">We do not take payments from any financial product company, insurance carrier, or advisor in exchange for editorial placement. When we link to a product or service, the affiliate relationship is disclosed at the top of the article, not buried at the bottom.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="commitment">
          <h3 class="commitment__title">Numbers, not vibes</h3>
          <p class="commitment__desc">Every claim about cost, return, or risk is cited and dated. When the data changes, we update the article and timestamp the revision. No piece on this site says "around $X" when the real number is knowable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="commitment">
          <h3 class="commitment__title">Positions, not "consider"</h3>
          <p class="commitment__desc">When the evidence supports a position, we take it. When it does not, we say so. We do not hedge for advertiser comfort or political balance. If we are wrong, we revise. We do not pretend to be neutral on things that are not neutral.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="commitment">
          <h3 class="commitment__title">Reviewer layer (rolling out)</h3>
          <p class="commitment__desc">Articles on money topics will progressively carry a "Reviewed by [Name, Credential]" line as we bring on credentialed financial professionals. Until then, articles in this section are bylined by the AfterChildren Editorial Desk or M. Holloway, the founder, and reflect independent research, not professional advice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE LINK TO -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="affiliates">
      <p class="affiliates__eyebrow">Affiliate disclosure</p>
      <h2 class="affiliates__title">What we link to, and what we earn.</h2>
      <p class="affiliates__intro">When we recommend a financial service, we link to it. When the link earns us a commission, we disclose it. We only link to services we have evaluated and believe in. We do not link to services we would not use ourselves.</p>
      <p class="affiliates__intro affiliates__intro--secondary">As this pillar develops, the partner list below will become live affiliate links. Until then, the list documents the services we are evaluating for inclusion. We will publish a review of each before any link goes live.</p>
      <div class="affiliates__list">
        <div class="affiliate">
          <h4 class="affiliate__name">Fiduciary advisor matching</h4>
          <p class="affiliate__desc">Fee-only fiduciaries near you, vetted, no commissions. Under evaluation: SmartAsset SmartAdvisor, Wealthramp, NAPFA directory.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="affiliate">
          <h4 class="affiliate__name">Online will &amp; estate</h4>
          <p class="affiliate__desc">Will, trust, healthcare directive, power of attorney. Under evaluation: Trust &amp; Will, Snug, FreeWill.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="affiliate">
          <h4 class="affiliate__name">Term life insurance</h4>
          <p class="affiliate__desc">For parents whose spouse depends on income through age 65–70. Under evaluation: Ladder Life, Haven Life, Bestow.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="affiliate">
          <h4 class="affiliate__name">Long-term care insurance</h4>
          <p class="affiliate__desc">Hybrid and traditional. Under evaluation: independent LTC broker network. We will not link to commission-driven captive agents.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="affiliate">
          <h4 class="affiliate__name">Retirement planning software</h4>
          <p class="affiliate__desc">Tools you can run yourself, before or alongside hiring an advisor. Under evaluation: Boldin (formerly NewRetirement), ProjectionLab.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="affiliate">
          <h4 class="affiliate__name">Medicare comparison</h4>
          <p class="affiliate__desc">Independent Medicare brokers, no carrier captives. Under evaluation: Chapter, HealthPilot, Medicare.gov plan finder (always free).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA: ASK A QUESTION -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="ask">
      <h2 class="ask__title">A question we should answer?</h2>
      <p class="ask__lede">If a Money topic is on your mind and not on the list above, note it. The most-asked questions become next month's articles. A public contact channel for reader questions is coming once the site has enough readers to make the conversation worth the inbox.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Newsletter />
</Base>

<style>
  /* =====================================
     Pillar page–specific styles
     Scoped here so they don't bloat global.
     ===================================== */

  /* PILLAR HERO */
  .pillar-hero {
    padding: var(--space-24) 0 var(--space-16);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--stone);
    max-width: 52rem;
  }
  .pillar-hero__eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-2xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ember);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
  .pillar-hero__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, var(--text-4xl));
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 100;
  }
  .pillar-hero__title em {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ember);
  }
  .pillar-hero__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ash);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }
  .pillar-hero__meta {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-2xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--ash);
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .pillar-hero__count {
    color: var(--ember);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .pillar-hero__sep {
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  /* WHERE TO START */
  .start-panel {
    padding: var(--space-24) 0 var(--space-16);
  }
  .start-panel__eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-2xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ember);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .start-panel__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    max-width: 36rem;
  }
  .start-panel__list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--stone);
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .start-panel__list {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      border-top: 0;
    }
  }
  .start-panel__item {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--stone);
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .start-panel__item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-6);
      padding: var(--space-8);
      border-bottom: 0;
      border-right: 1px solid var(--stone);
    }
    .start-panel__item:last-child {
      border-right: 0;
    }
  }
  .start-panel__num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ember);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .start-panel__step {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .start-panel__desc {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ash);
  }

  /* FEATURED MANIFESTO CARD */
  .featured {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-24);
  }
  .featured__eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-2xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ember);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .featured__card {
    display: block;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--bone);
    padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-8);
    border: 0;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.3s var(--ease-out);
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .featured__card {
      padding: var(--space-16) var(--space-12);
    }
  }
  .featured__card:hover {
    background: #1c2129;
    color: var(--bone);
  }
  .featured__meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
  .featured__tag {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-3xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink);
    background: #E07A4F;
    padding: 4px var(--space-3);
  }
  .featured__time {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-2xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: rgba(245, 241, 234, 0.6);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .featured__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, var(--text-3xl));
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    max-width: 44rem;
    color: var(--bone);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144;
  }
  .featured__excerpt {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(245, 241, 234, 0.75);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    max-width: 38rem;
  }
  .featured__cta {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-2xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #E07A4F;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }
  .featured__arrow {
    transition: transform 0.3s var(--ease-out);
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .featured__card:hover .featured__arrow {
    transform: translateX(6px);
  }

  /* SUB-PILLARS */
  .subpillars {
    padding: var(--space-24) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--stone);
  }
  .subpillars__eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-2xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ember);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .subpillars__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
    max-width: 36rem;
  }
  .subpillar {
    padding: var(--space-12) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--stone);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .subpillar {
      grid-template-columns: 18rem 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-12);
    }
  }
  .subpillar:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--stone);
  }
  .subpillar__head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }
  .subpillar__num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ember);
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .subpillar__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .subpillar__intro {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
  .subpillar__list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--stone);
  }
  .subpillar__list li {
    padding: var(--space-4) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--stone);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--ash);
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }
  .subpillar__list a {
    color: var(--ink);
    border-bottom: 0;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .subpillar__list a:hover {
    color: var(--ember);
  }
  .subpillar__item--live {
    color: var(--ink) !important;
  }
  .subpillar__item--live::before {
    content: "Live";
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-3xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
